t="0.55804">Reachability</keyword><keyword weight="0.67707">Timed automaton</keyword><keyword weight="0.54846">Liveness</keyword><keyword weight="0.529">Formal verification</keyword><keyword weight="0.47558">Bounded function</keyword></keywords><publisher>Springer-Verlag</publisher><abstract>In this paper we develop an approach to model-checking for timed automata via reachability testing. As our specification formalism, we consider a dense-time property language with clocks. This property language may be used to express safety and bounded liveness properties of real-time systems. We show how to automatically synthesize, for every formula ϕ, a test automaton Tϕ in such a way that checking whether a system S satisfies the property ϕ can be reduced to a reachability question over the system obtained by making Tϕ interact with S.</abstract></paper>